org.eclipse.january.dataset

Class SliceIterator

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.january.dataset.IndexIterator
      • org.eclipse.january.dataset.SliceIterator
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    NullIterator, StrideIterator

    public class SliceIterator
extends IndexIterator
    The SliceIterator class is use to run over a Slice of a Dataset. This is an Iterator thats allows the programmer to traverse the elements of a sliced Dataset and obtain the current position, the starts, steps, shapes. Moreover, there is possibilities to set the start point to begin at the wanted position.
